      "type": "heading",
      "value": "What are HTML Lists?"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "HTML lists are used to group related items in a structured way. They improve readability and organization of content."
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "Types of HTML Lists"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "value": "1. Unordered List (ul)"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Displays items with bullet points."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<ul>\n  <li>Apple</li>\n  <li>Banana</li>\n  <li>Cherry</li>\n</ul>"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "value": "2. Ordered List (ol)"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Displays items with numbers or letters."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<ol>\n  <li>First</li>\n  <li>Second</li>\n  <li>Third</li>\n</ol>"
    },
    {
      "type": "subheading",
      "value": "3. Description List (dl)"
    },
    {
      "type": "text",
      "value": "Used for terms and descriptions."
    },
    {
      "type": "code",
      "language": "html",
      "value": "<dl>\n  <dt>HTML</dt>\n  <dd>Markup language</dd>\n\n  <dt>CSS</dt>\n  <dd>Styling language</dd>\n</dl>"
    },
    {
      "type": "heading",
      "value": "List Attributes"
    },
    {
      "type": "table",
      "value": {
        "headers": ["Attribute", "Used In", "Description"],
